# Security Checklist: {{display_name}}

- [ ] Address encoding is canonical and unambiguous
- [ ] Derivation path is documented with hardened vs non-hardened boundaries
- [ ] Signing inputs are clearly defined
- [ ] Hashing step is specified, if any
- [ ] Domain separation or message prefixing is specified, if any
- [ ] Canonical serialization is specified before signing
- [ ] Test vectors cover both expected and malformed inputs
- [ ] Chain-specific edge cases are listed in docs
